# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Trading Agent — .gitignore
# Goal: source-of-truth for code, but NEVER commit secrets, runtime
# state, models, or large generated artefacts.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# ── Secrets & environment ────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.production.example
*.secret
credentials.json
*.pem
*.key
oci_trader_key
oci_trader_key.pub
env.backup
db.backup

# ── Python ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg
*.egg-info/
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/

# ── Test / lint / type-check caches ──────────────────────────────
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.tox/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
.hypothesis/

# ── Virtual environments ─────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
env/
ENV/
.venv/

# ── Trading runtime state ────────────────────────────────────────
# Database (contains trade history, can be regenerated from logs)
data/*.db
data/*.db-*
data/*.sqlite
data/*.sqlite3

# Model artefacts (large, regenerate via training/)
models/*.pkl
models/*.pt
models/*.joblib
models/*.onnx

# Backtest scratch state
**/market_data.pkl
**/cycle_state.pkl
*.cache

# 2026-05-14: self-sufficiency ledger is per-deployment runtime state,
# not source. Each operator's cumulative realised P&L stays local.
data/self_sufficiency.json

# 2026-05-14: ad-hoc prepare_dataset CLI logs accidentally landed in
# data/. Build logs belong under logs/, but keep this rule so a stray
# write here can never be committed.
data/prepare_dataset_*.log

# 2026-05-15: cooldowns.json is per-deployment runtime state written by
# core.cooldown_persistence after every stop-out / blacklist / rejection
# update. Must not be committed -- snapshots are deployment-specific and
# would defeat the daily-reset semantics if shared across hosts.
data/cooldowns.json

# 2026-05-17: trailing_stops.json (P1 #15) -- per-deployment in-flight
# TrailingStop state. Same per-host runtime contract as cooldowns.json.
data/trailing_stops.json

# 2026-05-17: runtime_state.json (P2 restart-cluster) -- per-deployment
# intraday runtime state (per-strategy breaker, open-rate window, TP
# streak). Same per-host runtime contract.
data/runtime_state.json

# ── Logs (all subdirs and roots) ────────────────────────────────
logs/**/*.log
logs/**/*.csv
logs/**/*.md
logs/**/*.json
logs/**/*.txt
logs/**/*.pkl
logs/**/*.yaml
logs/**/*.yml
# Keep folder structure so first clone has the empty dirs
!logs/**/.gitkeep

# Per-day daemon stdout/stderr captures
daemon_*.log
agent_*.log
battery_*.log

# ── PID and lock files ──────────────────────────────────────────
*.pid
*.lock
*.daemon.lock
emergency_stop
STOP

# ── IDE & OS noise ──────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ── Failed alert spool (auto-replays on boot) ──────────────────
.failed_alerts/
.alerts_spool/

# ── Misc generated reports kept outside logs/ ──────────────────
audit_*.md
checkpoint_*.md

# ── Cloud sync (research-pod outputs mirrored to laptop) ───────
# logs/cloud_sync/  files already caught by logs/**/* rules above,
# but list the dir explicitly so it's discoverable.
logs/cloud_sync/
data/local_cloud_mirror/

# ── Backtest one-off runs at root (legacy, will move to logs/archive) ──
backtest_run_*/
